      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HI LO RAIN (1) box seated before sticking on well to finish 4 lengths away in second (29.72) at The Gardens in a Grade 4/5 over 515m. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Well-placed to take this out. BONUS ETHICS (2) is a capable type and proved too strong last time to win by 1.5 lengths at Richmond in a handy 22.80 beating No Spark Left. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in her latest win. Has definite claims. WHISKY BENT (3) doesn't show much early dash but winds into his races, two back missing the frame but last time hitting the line hard to place when third (30.30) in a Grade 5 at this track last time. Hard to beat again. RAINBOW RAY (8) won as favourite last time – cannot be taken lightly.",
